Tips


When you first begin your business, ask the person who recruited you to help you organize your online and offline events.





Warnings


Although social networking sites are a good place to meet people and promote your business, don't spend all your time advertising your business. You will alienate your friends and contacts if you come across as a pushy salesperson.
Carefully read the policies, procedures and terms of your agreement with the company. You should understand what types of advertising and marketing you can use to promote your business. Most companies and the law prohibit you from sending unsolicited email to promote your products.





